The '''Achang language''' (autonym: ''{{IPA|ŋa˨˩tʂhaŋ˨˩}}''; {{zh|阿昌}}) is a [[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman language]] spoken by the [[Achang people|Achang]] (also known as Maingtha and Ngochang) in [[Yunnan]], [[China]].
==Distribution== Achang is spoken in the following locations (阿昌语简志):
*[[Longchuan County, Yunnan|Longchuan County]], [[Dehong Prefecture]] **Husa 户撒 *[[Lianghe County]], Dehong Prefecture **Zhedao 遮岛 **Xiangsong 襄宋 **Dachang 大厂 *[[Luxi City]], Dehong Prefecture **Jiangdong 江东 *[[Longling County]], [[Baoshan, Yunnan|Baoshan]]
The ''Xiandao'' 仙岛 dialect (100 speakers; autonym ''{{IPA|kʰan˧˩tau˧˩}}'') is spoken in the following two locations in [[Yingjiang County]], Dehong Prefecture (''Xiandaoyu Yanjiu'').
*Xiandaozhai 仙岛寨, Mangmian Village 芒面村, Jiemao Township 姐冒乡<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vindex.aspx?departmentid=150440</ref> *Meng'ezhai 勐俄寨, Mangxian Village 芒线村, Jiemao Township 姐冒乡<ref>http://www.ynszxc.gov.cn/villagePage/vindex.aspx?departmentid=150426</ref>
